# Python-Arduino Servo Control

## Overview
This project controls an SG90 servo motor using Python and Arduino through serial communication. It has two modes:
- Enter servo angles (0–180)
- Control the servo using the left and right arrow keys

## What I Learned
- Python ↔ Arduino serial communication
- Servo control using the Servo library
- Keyboard input in Python
- Input validation
- Using `min()` and `max()` to keep values between 0 and 180

## AI Assistance
- GitHub Copilot: Suggested code improvements, including using `min()` and `max()` to keep the servo angle between 0° and 180°.
- ChatGPT: Helped me understand concepts, review my code, and troubleshoot the Servo library setup in PlatformIO.

